<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="621" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[691,1284,2230,2649]" lastBlockId="23.[81,1287,2657,3477]" pageId="23" pageNumber="621">
Originally described in genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1167,1278,2345,2374]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="621" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gerbillus</taxonomicName>
, and later moved by G. S. Shortridge to his newly described genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shortridge" authorityYear="1942" box="[1023,1163,2419,2453]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="621" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gerbillurus</taxonomicName>
in 1942, the taxon 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Smith" authorityYear="1836" box="[843,917,2458,2492]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="621" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="paeba">paeba</taxonomicName>
is now treated under ge- nus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1897" box="[760,902,2506,2531]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbilliscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="621" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Gerbilliscus</taxonomicName>
as a result of molecular/ chromosomal studies by P. Chevret and G. Dobigny in 2005, P. Colangelo and team in 2007, and L. Granjon and colleagues in 2012. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Smith" authorityYear="1836" box="[169,278,2657,2691]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="23" pageNumber="621" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="paeba">G. paeba</taxonomicName>
is thought to be close to G. tytonis. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
